<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="4" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[264,1322,1724,1830]" box="[264,389,1724,1749]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis box="[264,389,1724,1749]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Etymology</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[264,1322,1724,1830]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">This species is named after the paler and more shining apices of the elytra (patched = maculata).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="5" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[264,1323,284,510]" box="[264,392,284,309]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<emphasis box="[264,392,284,309]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Discussion</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[264,1323,284,510]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<taxonomicName authority="Geisthardt &amp; Day, 2004" authorityName="Geisthardt &amp; Day" authorityYear="2004" box="[312,586,324,349]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Lampyroidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maculata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[312,586,324,349]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Lampyroidea maculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[596,689,324,350]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is the third Iranian species of this genus. Compared with two other species recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[707,757,364,390]" name="Iran" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Iran</collectingCountry>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Geisthardt" authorityName="Geisthardt" authorityYear="1988" box="[770,1052,364,390]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Lampyroidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="antennalis">
<emphasis box="[770,923,364,389]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">L. antennalis</emphasis>
Geisthardt
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Olivier" authorityName="Olivier" authorityYear="1907" box="[1109,1318,364,390]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Lampyroidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="persica">
<emphasis box="[1109,1226,364,389]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">L. persica</emphasis>
Olivier
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Geisthardt &amp; Day, 2004" authorityName="Geisthardt &amp; Day" authorityYear="2004" box="[264,535,404,429]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Lampyroidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maculata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[264,535,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Lampyroidea maculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[543,633,404,430]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is much greater in size, has slender antennae, and the apex of the elytra is paler and somewhat reflective. The most important differences are given in table 1.
</paragraph>
